To view or customize your own version of this license, visit the License Builder at:
https://firstdonoharm.dev/build/

The Hippocratic License is an ethical open source software license that grants software rights while imposing ethical conditions. It is designed to confront the potential harms and abuses technology can have on fundamental human rights.

Key ethical requirements include:
- Not infringing upon any person's right to life or security of person
- Prohibiting slavery, torture, and forced labor
- Preventing discrimination
- Restricting use that violates fundamental human rights

For more information about the Hippocratic License, visit:
https://firstdonoharm.dev/
